The paper proposes a convolutional neural network architecture for geometric matching, which involves feature extraction, matching, and parameter estimation. This work is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of synthetic imagery and demonstrates state-of-the-art results on a challenging dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The problem of geometric matching is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM), which are other possible sub-categories.
